[2026-03-18T17:52:46.249Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WnHBpnvYFko6UL4CMFQnL4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Execution Lifecycle Analysis - Complete Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here is the comprehensive understanding of the execution lifecycle:\n\n### 1. EXECUTION STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n#### Valid States (Database Schema)\n- **queued** (default initial state)\n- **running** (dispatched to worker, currently executing)\n- **completed** (successful execution)\n- **failed** (execution failure or timeout)\n- **cancelled** (execution killed on demand)\n\n#### State Transition Flow\n```\nqueued → running → completed\n       ↘        ↘ failed\n                ↘ cancelled\n\nSpecial cases:\n- queued → queued: Re-queuing on worker busy/disconnect\n- running → queued: Re-queuing after worker disconnect (up to MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES=2)\n```\n\n#### State Transition Points in Code\n\n**Queued → Running (dispatcher.ts, line 442-445)**\n- Location: `dispatchToWorker()` method\n- Triggers: New execution assigned to idle worker\n- DB update: `status: 'running', startedAt: new Date().toISOString()`\n\n**Running → Terminal States (dispatcher.ts, line 92-143)**\n- Location: Pool 'complete' event handler\n- Triggers: Worker reports `ExecComplete` message\n- Terminal states: 'completed', 'failed', 'cancelled'\n- DB update fields:\n  - `status` (maps worker status to DB status)\n  - `completedAt: new Date().toISOString()`\n  - `durationMs: msg.durationMs`\n  - `claudeSessionId: msg.sessionId`\n  - `costUsd: msg.totalCostUsd ?? 0`\n\n**Running → Queued (Retries)**\n- Location: Two retry paths:\n  1. Worker busy nack (line 175-211): Worker rejects assignment mid-dispatch\n  2. Worker disconnect (line 214-281): Worker disconnects during execution (up to 2 retries)\n- DB error message includes retry count: `Worker disconnected (retry 1/2)`\n\n**Running → Failed (Permanent Failure)**\n- Location: Worker disconnect retries exhausted (line 252-270)\n- DB updates:\n  - `status: 'failed'`\n  - `errorMessage: 'Worker disconnected (retries exhausted: 2/2)'`\n  - `completedAt: new Date().toISOString()`\n\n### 2. CURRENT LOGGING PATTERNS ACROSS PROJECT\n\n#### Dispatcher Logging (packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts)\n\n**Submission Phase (line 342-347)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  executionId: request.executionId,\n  personaId: request.personaId,\n  ...(request.eventId ? { eventId: request.eventId } : {}),\n}, 'Execution submitted');\n```\n\n**Dispatch Phase (line 459-464)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  workerId,\n  executionId: request.executionId,\n  personaId: request.personaId,\n  ...(request.eventId ? { eventId: request.eventId } : {}),\n}, 'Execution dispatched to worker');\n```\n\n**Completion Phase (line 317-323 in workerPool.ts)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  workerId,\n  executionId: msg.executionId,\n  status: msg.status,\n  durationMs: msg.durationMs,\n  ...(msg.phaseTimings ? { phaseTimings: msg.phaseTimings } : {}),\n}, 'Execution complete');\n```\n\n**Error Handling**\n```typescript\nlogger.warn({ err, executionId: request.executionId }, 'Failed to ...');\nlogger.error({ err, executionId: request.executionId }, 'Failed to ...');\n```\n\n#### Worker Executor Logging (packages/worker/src/executor.ts)\n\n**Start Phase (line 130-135)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  executionId: assignment.executionId,\n  personaId: assignment.personaId,\n  sandboxDir: sandbox.sandboxDir,\n  timeoutMs: assignment.config.timeoutMs,\n}, 'Starting execution');\n```\n\n**Completion Phase (line 243-251)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  executionId: assignment.executionId,\n  exitCode,\n  durationMs,\n  status,\n  sessionId: this.sessionId,\n  totalCostUsd: this.totalCostUsd,\n  phaseTimings,\n}, 'Execution finished');\n```\n\n#### Event Processor Logging (packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts)\n\n**Event Dispatch (line 284-290)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  eventId: event.id,\n  personaId: persona.id,\n  executionId: request.executionId,\n  eventType: event.eventType,\n  useCaseId: match.useCaseId,\n}, 'Event dispatched to persona');\n```\n\n**Tick Completion (line 327-334)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  tickDurationMs,\n  eventsFetched,\n  matchesFound,\n  delivered,\n  skipped,\n  failed\n}, 'Event processor tick complete');\n```\n\n**Logging Style Convention**\n- Uses Pino logger (structured JSON logging)\n- Context object as first parameter with relevant IDs/metrics\n- Human-readable message as second parameter\n- No emoji usage\n- Includes operation name (`op: 'updateExecution:queued'`) for tracking specific DB operations\n\n### 3. KEY FILES AND THEIR ROLES\n\n#### Orchestrator Package\n\n**dispatcher.ts** (585 lines)\n- Central hub for execution lifecycle management\n- In-memory tracking: `active` map for real-time executions\n- Queue management: `queue` array for pending executions\n- State transitions: submit → queue → dispatch → running → terminal\n- Re-queueing logic with disconnect retry count tracking\n\n**workerPool.ts** (412 lines)\n- WebSocket connection management for workers\n- Worker lifecycle: connect → hello → ready → executing → disconnect\n- Metrics tracking: connections, disconnections, parse failures, heartbeat health\n- Event emission to dispatcher for state changes\n\n**eventProcessor.ts** (337 lines)\n- Periodic event processing loop (2s interval with on-demand nudging)\n- Event state management: pending → processing → delivered/failed/partial\n- Concurrency limiting per persona\n- Batch optimization with transaction-level DB operations\n\n**dispatchPipeline.ts** (267 lines)\n- Composable pipeline stages:\n  1. Resolve token (OAuth or stored)\n  2. Resolve persona (DB lookup + credential decryption)\n  3. Assemble payload (build env + prompt + network policy)\n  4. Build assignment (create ExecAssign message)\n\n**db/executions.ts** (183 lines)\n- CRUD operations for `persona_executions` table\n- State transitions: queued → running → completed/failed/cancelled\n- Terminal status detection for metrics recording\n- Batch counting for concurrency limits\n\n**db/schema.ts** (341 lines)\n- Execution table schema:\n  - Status: CHECK constraint validates states\n  - Timestamps: createdAt, startedAt, completedAt\n  - Performance: inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, durationMs\n  - Correlation: eventId, triggerId, useCaseId\n- Indices for: persona_id, status, created_at + status\n\n#### Worker Package\n\n**executor.ts** (273 lines)\n- Execution state machine: idle → busy → cleanup\n- Sandbox lifecycle: prepare → execute → cleanup\n- Phase timing tracking: sandboxSetup, credentialInjection, proxyStartup, cliRuntime, cleanup\n- Output buffering and line parsing\n- Timeout enforcement and cancellation via SIGTERM/SIGKILL\n\n**connection.ts** (281 lines)\n- WebSocket client for worker-to-orchestrator communication\n- State tracking: connected/reconnecting/disconnected\n- Message routing: assign → execute, cancel → kill, shutdown → graceful exit\n- Automatic reconnection with exponential backoff (1s → 30s)\n\n**index.ts** (164 lines)\n- Worker main entry point\n- Coordination between Connection and Executor\n- Signal handlers for graceful shutdown\n- Health probe server setup\n\n#### Shared Package\n\n**types.ts** (347 lines)\n- Execution types:\n  - `PersonaExecution`: Full execution record\n  - `ExecRequest`: Request produced to Kafka by client\n  - `ExecResult`: Result sent to Kafka by orchestrator\n  - `WorkerInfo`: Worker status tracking\n- Event types with state machine validation:\n  - Event status: pending | processing | delivered | skipped | failed | partial | partial-retry\n  - Transition validation function: `validateEventTransition(from, to)`\n- Kafka topics: exec-requests, exec-output, exec-lifecycle, exec-progress, events, dlq\n\n**protocol.ts** (230 lines)\n- WebSocket message types for orchestrator ↔ worker\n- Worker → Orchestrator: hello, ready, stdout, stderr, complete, progress, event, busy, heartbeat\n- Orchestrator → Worker: ack, assign, cancel, shutdown, heartbeat\n- Message validators for runtime safety\n\n### 4. EXECUTION OBJECT STRUCTURE\n\n#### Database Record (PersonaExecution)\n```typescript\n{\n  id: string;                    // nanoid\n  projectId: string;            // default 'default'\n  personaId: string;            // references persona\n  triggerId: string | null;     // manual, schedule, webhook, chain\n  useCaseId: string | null;     // business context\n  eventId: string | null;       // event↔execution correlation\n  status: string;               // queued | running | completed | failed | cancelled\n  inputData: string | null;     // serialized input\n  outputData: string | null;    // accumulated stdout\n  claudeSessionId: string | null;\n  modelUsed: string | null;\n  inputTokens: number;          // from Claude\n  outputTokens: number;         // from Claude\n  costUsd: number;              // total execution cost\n  errorMessage: string | null;  // failure reason\n  durationMs: number | null;    // wall-clock time\n  retryOfExecutionId: string | null;\n  retryCount: number;\n  startedAt: string | null;     // ISO timestamp\n  completedAt: string | null;   // ISO timestamp\n  createdAt: string;            // ISO timestamp\n}\n```\n\n#### In-Memory Execution Tracking (Dispatcher)\n```typescript\nActiveExecution {\n  workerId: string;\n  startedAt: number;              // Date.now()\n  output: string[];               // buffered stdout lines\n  status: 'running' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled';\n  progress?: ProgressInfo;        // phase, percent, detail, updatedAt\n  completedAt?: number;\n  exitCode?: number;\n  durationMs?: number;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  totalCostUsd?: number;\n  phaseTimings?: PhaseTimings;\n  request?: ExecRequest;          // for re-queueing\n  disconnectRetries?: number;     // retry count tracker\n}\n```\n\n### 5. EXECUTION LIFECYCLE SEQUENCE DIAGRAM\n\n```\nClient (Vibeman)\n     |\n     | ExecRequest (Kafka)\n     v\nDispatcher.submit()\n  ├─ Create DB record: status='queued'\n  ├─ Track: executionTenant[executionId] = projectId\n  └─ Push to: this.queue\n\nprocessQueue()\n  ├─ Guard: dispatching flag (prevent concurrent races)\n  ├─ Get idle worker\n  └─ dispatchToWorker()\n       ├─ Stage 1: resolveToken()\n       ├─ Stage 2-4: ExecutionPreparer.prepare()\n       │   ├─ resolvePersona() → decrypt credentials\n       │   ├─ assemblePayload() → build env + prompt\n       │   └─ buildAssignment() → create ExecAssign\n       ├─ Update DB: status='running', startedAt\n       ├─ Track in-memory: this.active[id] = {...}\n       └─ workerPool.assign(workerId, ExecAssign)\n\nWorker (Connected via WSS)\n  ├─ Receive ExecAssign\n  ├─ Executor.execute()\n  │   ├─ prepareSandbox()\n  │   ├─ injectCredentialsViaFile()\n  │   ├─ startFilterProxy() (if network policy)\n  │   ├─ spawn CLI process\n  │   ├─ Listen stdout/stderr\n  │   ├─ Wait for process exit\n  │   └─ Cleanup (sandbox, creds, proxy)\n  └─ Connection.sendComplete(status, exitCode, durationMs, ...)\n\nOrchestrator (Complete Event)\n  ├─ Dispatcher pool.on('complete')\n  ├─ Produce EXEC_LIFECYCLE to Kafka\n  ├─ Update DB:\n  │   ├─ status = 'completed'|'failed'|'cancelled'\n  │   ├─ completedAt, durationMs, costUsd\n  │   └─ Increment daily_metrics\n  ├─ Update in-memory: this.active[id].status\n  ├─ Schedule cleanup: delete from active (30s)\n  └─ processQueue() → dispatch next\n\nRe-queueing Paths:\n1. Worker Busy (NACK):\n   - Update DB: status='queued'\n   - Unshift to queue: front of line priority\n   - processQueue() → retry dispatch\n\n2. Worker Disconnect During Execution:\n   - If retries < 2:\n     - Update DB: status='queued', errorMessage=(retry X/2)\n     - Increment disconnectRetries counter\n     - Unshift to queue → processQueue()\n   - Else (retries exhausted):\n     - Update DB: status='failed', errorMessage=(exhausted)\n     - Produce EXEC_LIFECYCLE failure to Kafka\n\n3. Assignment Failure:\n   - Update DB: status='queued'\n   - Unshift to queue → processQueue()\n```\n\n### 6. RETRIES AND RECOVERY MECHANISMS\n\n#### Disconnect Retry Logic (dispatcher.ts, lines 214-281)\n- **Trigger**: Worker disconnects while executing\n- **Max Retries**: 2 (MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES)\n- **Tracking**: Via `disconnectRetries` counter in ActiveExecution\n- **DB Update**: Error message includes retry count: `Worker disconnected (retry 1/2)`\n- **Completion**: After 2 retries exhausted → permanent failure\n\n#### Busy Nack Retry (dispatcher.ts, lines 175-211)\n- **Trigger**: Worker sends 'busy' message (cannot accept assignment)\n- **Action**: Remove from active, re-queue to front, update DB to 'queued'\n- **Reason**: Worker hit internal constraints (concurrency, resource limits)\n\n#### Event Processing Retry (eventProcessor.ts, lines 299-317)\n- **Partial Delivery**: Some matches succeed, others fail/throttled\n- **Status**: 'partial-retry' or deferred for backoff retry\n- **Backoff**: Via `deferEventForRetry()` which uses exponential backoff\n- **Concurrency Limiting**: Per-persona max_concurrent enforcement\n\n#### Orphaned Event Recovery (eventProcessor.ts, lines 32-50)\n- **On Startup**: Reset all events in 'processing' state → 'pending'\n- **Periodic Reaping**: Every 60s, reset stale processing events (>120s old)\n- **Guard**: Prevents events stuck in processing from blocking forever\n\n### 7. LOGGING SUMMARY\n\n#### Current Logging Coverage\n\n| Phase | Level | Message | File:Line |\n|-------|-------|---------|-----------|\n| Submit | INFO | 'Execution submitted' | dispatcher.ts:343 |\n| Dispatch | INFO | 'Execution dispatched to worker' | dispatcher.ts:459 |\n| Complete (worker) | INFO | 'Execution finished' | executor.ts:243 |\n| Complete (pool) | INFO | 'Execution complete' | workerPool.ts:317 |\n| Event dispatch | INFO | 'Event dispatched to persona' | eventProcessor.ts:284 |\n| Stderr | WARN | 'Execution stderr' | dispatcher.ts:88 |\n| Worker busy | WARN | 'Worker rejected assignment' | dispatcher.ts:176 |\n| Disconnect retry | WARN | 'Worker disconnected, re-queueing' | dispatcher.ts:222 |\n| Retries exhausted | ERROR | 'Retries exhausted' | dispatcher.ts:254 |\n| DB operation fail | WARN | 'Failed to update execution status' | dispatcher.ts:184 |\n| Kafka produce fail | ERROR | 'Failed to produce to Kafka' | dispatcher.ts:102 |\n| Event tick | INFO | 'Event processor tick complete' | eventProcessor.ts:327 |\n\n#### Logging Context Pattern\n- Always includes `executionId` (or `eventId`) for correlation\n- Includes operation context: `op: 'updateExecution:queued'`\n- Phase information: `status: 'completed'`, `exitCode: 0`\n- Timing info: `durationMs`, `tickDurationMs`, `phaseTimings`\n- Worker context: `workerId` where relevant\n\n### 8. KEY EXECUTION-RELATED FILES\n\n#### Orchestrator Source\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts` (585 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/workerPool.ts` (412 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts` (337 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatchPipeline.ts` (267 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts` (183 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (341 lines)\n\n#### Worker Source\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/executor.ts` (273 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/connection.ts` (281 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/index.ts` (164 lines)\n\n#### Shared Source\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/types.ts` (347 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts` (230 lines)\n\nThis comprehensive analysis provides the foundation for understanding and enhancing the execution lifecycle tracking, logging, and state management across the entire personas-cloud system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a755d60c4a50a9868 (use SendMessage with to: 'a755d60c4a50a9868' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71013\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 83417</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d073280e-6082-4db5-95e6-287c162efeec","uuid":"4434e5f7-6725-456a-a5d1-b896b0f8e67e","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:52:46.171Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand the execution lifecycle. I need to find:\n\n1. All state transitions for executions (queued, running, completed, failed, cancelled, re-queued)\n2. Current logging patterns used across the project\n3. The dispatcher, worker pool, event processor, and any execution-related files\n4. The types/interfaces for executions\n5. Any existing state/status enums or types\n\nFocus on these directories:\n- packages/orchestrator/src/ (especially dispatcher.ts, workerPool.ts, eventProcessor.ts, dispatchPipeline.ts)\n- packages/shared/src/ (especially types.ts, protocol.ts)\n- packages/worker/src/ (especially executor.ts, connection.ts)\n\nRead the full contents of the key files. I need to understand:\n- What states an execution can be in\n- Where state transitions happen\n- What logging currently exists at those transition points\n- The structure of execution objects (IDs, metadata, etc.)\n","agentId":"a755d60c4a50a9868","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Execution Lifecycle Analysis - Complete Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here is the comprehensive understanding of the execution lifecycle:\n\n### 1. EXECUTION STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n#### Valid States (Database Schema)\n- **queued** (default initial state)\n- **running** (dispatched to worker, currently executing)\n- **completed** (successful execution)\n- **failed** (execution failure or timeout)\n- **cancelled** (execution killed on demand)\n\n#### State Transition Flow\n```\nqueued → running → completed\n       ↘        ↘ failed\n                ↘ cancelled\n\nSpecial cases:\n- queued → queued: Re-queuing on worker busy/disconnect\n- running → queued: Re-queuing after worker disconnect (up to MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES=2)\n```\n\n#### State Transition Points in Code\n\n**Queued → Running (dispatcher.ts, line 442-445)**\n- Location: `dispatchToWorker()` method\n- Triggers: New execution assigned to idle worker\n- DB update: `status: 'running', startedAt: new Date().toISOString()`\n\n**Running → Terminal States (dispatcher.ts, line 92-143)**\n- Location: Pool 'complete' event handler\n- Triggers: Worker reports `ExecComplete` message\n- Terminal states: 'completed', 'failed', 'cancelled'\n- DB update fields:\n  - `status` (maps worker status to DB status)\n  - `completedAt: new Date().toISOString()`\n  - `durationMs: msg.durationMs`\n  - `claudeSessionId: msg.sessionId`\n  - `costUsd: msg.totalCostUsd ?? 0`\n\n**Running → Queued (Retries)**\n- Location: Two retry paths:\n  1. Worker busy nack (line 175-211): Worker rejects assignment mid-dispatch\n  2. Worker disconnect (line 214-281): Worker disconnects during execution (up to 2 retries)\n- DB error message includes retry count: `Worker disconnected (retry 1/2)`\n\n**Running → Failed (Permanent Failure)**\n- Location: Worker disconnect retries exhausted (line 252-270)\n- DB updates:\n  - `status: 'failed'`\n  - `errorMessage: 'Worker disconnected (retries exhausted: 2/2)'`\n  - `completedAt: new Date().toISOString()`\n\n### 2. CURRENT LOGGING PATTERNS ACROSS PROJECT\n\n#### Dispatcher Logging (packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts)\n\n**Submission Phase (line 342-347)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  executionId: request.executionId,\n  personaId: request.personaId,\n  ...(request.eventId ? { eventId: request.eventId } : {}),\n}, 'Execution submitted');\n```\n\n**Dispatch Phase (line 459-464)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  workerId,\n  executionId: request.executionId,\n  personaId: request.personaId,\n  ...(request.eventId ? { eventId: request.eventId } : {}),\n}, 'Execution dispatched to worker');\n```\n\n**Completion Phase (line 317-323 in workerPool.ts)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  workerId,\n  executionId: msg.executionId,\n  status: msg.status,\n  durationMs: msg.durationMs,\n  ...(msg.phaseTimings ? { phaseTimings: msg.phaseTimings } : {}),\n}, 'Execution complete');\n```\n\n**Error Handling**\n```typescript\nlogger.warn({ err, executionId: request.executionId }, 'Failed to ...');\nlogger.error({ err, executionId: request.executionId }, 'Failed to ...');\n```\n\n#### Worker Executor Logging (packages/worker/src/executor.ts)\n\n**Start Phase (line 130-135)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  executionId: assignment.executionId,\n  personaId: assignment.personaId,\n  sandboxDir: sandbox.sandboxDir,\n  timeoutMs: assignment.config.timeoutMs,\n}, 'Starting execution');\n```\n\n**Completion Phase (line 243-251)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  executionId: assignment.executionId,\n  exitCode,\n  durationMs,\n  status,\n  sessionId: this.sessionId,\n  totalCostUsd: this.totalCostUsd,\n  phaseTimings,\n}, 'Execution finished');\n```\n\n#### Event Processor Logging (packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts)\n\n**Event Dispatch (line 284-290)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  eventId: event.id,\n  personaId: persona.id,\n  executionId: request.executionId,\n  eventType: event.eventType,\n  useCaseId: match.useCaseId,\n}, 'Event dispatched to persona');\n```\n\n**Tick Completion (line 327-334)**\n```typescript\nlogger.info({\n  tickDurationMs,\n  eventsFetched,\n  matchesFound,\n  delivered,\n  skipped,\n  failed\n}, 'Event processor tick complete');\n```\n\n**Logging Style Convention**\n- Uses Pino logger (structured JSON logging)\n- Context object as first parameter with relevant IDs/metrics\n- Human-readable message as second parameter\n- No emoji usage\n- Includes operation name (`op: 'updateExecution:queued'`) for tracking specific DB operations\n\n### 3. KEY FILES AND THEIR ROLES\n\n#### Orchestrator Package\n\n**dispatcher.ts** (585 lines)\n- Central hub for execution lifecycle management\n- In-memory tracking: `active` map for real-time executions\n- Queue management: `queue` array for pending executions\n- State transitions: submit → queue → dispatch → running → terminal\n- Re-queueing logic with disconnect retry count tracking\n\n**workerPool.ts** (412 lines)\n- WebSocket connection management for workers\n- Worker lifecycle: connect → hello → ready → executing → disconnect\n- Metrics tracking: connections, disconnections, parse failures, heartbeat health\n- Event emission to dispatcher for state changes\n\n**eventProcessor.ts** (337 lines)\n- Periodic event processing loop (2s interval with on-demand nudging)\n- Event state management: pending → processing → delivered/failed/partial\n- Concurrency limiting per persona\n- Batch optimization with transaction-level DB operations\n\n**dispatchPipeline.ts** (267 lines)\n- Composable pipeline stages:\n  1. Resolve token (OAuth or stored)\n  2. Resolve persona (DB lookup + credential decryption)\n  3. Assemble payload (build env + prompt + network policy)\n  4. Build assignment (create ExecAssign message)\n\n**db/executions.ts** (183 lines)\n- CRUD operations for `persona_executions` table\n- State transitions: queued → running → completed/failed/cancelled\n- Terminal status detection for metrics recording\n- Batch counting for concurrency limits\n\n**db/schema.ts** (341 lines)\n- Execution table schema:\n  - Status: CHECK constraint validates states\n  - Timestamps: createdAt, startedAt, completedAt\n  - Performance: inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, durationMs\n  - Correlation: eventId, triggerId, useCaseId\n- Indices for: persona_id, status, created_at + status\n\n#### Worker Package\n\n**executor.ts** (273 lines)\n- Execution state machine: idle → busy → cleanup\n- Sandbox lifecycle: prepare → execute → cleanup\n- Phase timing tracking: sandboxSetup, credentialInjection, proxyStartup, cliRuntime, cleanup\n- Output buffering and line parsing\n- Timeout enforcement and cancellation via SIGTERM/SIGKILL\n\n**connection.ts** (281 lines)\n- WebSocket client for worker-to-orchestrator communication\n- State tracking: connected/reconnecting/disconnected\n- Message routing: assign → execute, cancel → kill, shutdown → graceful exit\n- Automatic reconnection with exponential backoff (1s → 30s)\n\n**index.ts** (164 lines)\n- Worker main entry point\n- Coordination between Connection and Executor\n- Signal handlers for graceful shutdown\n- Health probe server setup\n\n#### Shared Package\n\n**types.ts** (347 lines)\n- Execution types:\n  - `PersonaExecution`: Full execution record\n  - `ExecRequest`: Request produced to Kafka by client\n  - `ExecResult`: Result sent to Kafka by orchestrator\n  - `WorkerInfo`: Worker status tracking\n- Event types with state machine validation:\n  - Event status: pending | processing | delivered | skipped | failed | partial | partial-retry\n  - Transition validation function: `validateEventTransition(from, to)`\n- Kafka topics: exec-requests, exec-output, exec-lifecycle, exec-progress, events, dlq\n\n**protocol.ts** (230 lines)\n- WebSocket message types for orchestrator ↔ worker\n- Worker → Orchestrator: hello, ready, stdout, stderr, complete, progress, event, busy, heartbeat\n- Orchestrator → Worker: ack, assign, cancel, shutdown, heartbeat\n- Message validators for runtime safety\n\n### 4. EXECUTION OBJECT STRUCTURE\n\n#### Database Record (PersonaExecution)\n```typescript\n{\n  id: string;                    // nanoid\n  projectId: string;            // default 'default'\n  personaId: string;            // references persona\n  triggerId: string | null;     // manual, schedule, webhook, chain\n  useCaseId: string | null;     // business context\n  eventId: string | null;       // event↔execution correlation\n  status: string;               // queued | running | completed | failed | cancelled\n  inputData: string | null;     // serialized input\n  outputData: string | null;    // accumulated stdout\n  claudeSessionId: string | null;\n  modelUsed: string | null;\n  inputTokens: number;          // from Claude\n  outputTokens: number;         // from Claude\n  costUsd: number;              // total execution cost\n  errorMessage: string | null;  // failure reason\n  durationMs: number | null;    // wall-clock time\n  retryOfExecutionId: string | null;\n  retryCount: number;\n  startedAt: string | null;     // ISO timestamp\n  completedAt: string | null;   // ISO timestamp\n  createdAt: string;            // ISO timestamp\n}\n```\n\n#### In-Memory Execution Tracking (Dispatcher)\n```typescript\nActiveExecution {\n  workerId: string;\n  startedAt: number;              // Date.now()\n  output: string[];               // buffered stdout lines\n  status: 'running' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled';\n  progress?: ProgressInfo;        // phase, percent, detail, updatedAt\n  completedAt?: number;\n  exitCode?: number;\n  durationMs?: number;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  totalCostUsd?: number;\n  phaseTimings?: PhaseTimings;\n  request?: ExecRequest;          // for re-queueing\n  disconnectRetries?: number;     // retry count tracker\n}\n```\n\n### 5. EXECUTION LIFECYCLE SEQUENCE DIAGRAM\n\n```\nClient (Vibeman)\n     |\n     | ExecRequest (Kafka)\n     v\nDispatcher.submit()\n  ├─ Create DB record: status='queued'\n  ├─ Track: executionTenant[executionId] = projectId\n  └─ Push to: this.queue\n\nprocessQueue()\n  ├─ Guard: dispatching flag (prevent concurrent races)\n  ├─ Get idle worker\n  └─ dispatchToWorker()\n       ├─ Stage 1: resolveToken()\n       ├─ Stage 2-4: ExecutionPreparer.prepare()\n       │   ├─ resolvePersona() → decrypt credentials\n       │   ├─ assemblePayload() → build env + prompt\n       │   └─ buildAssignment() → create ExecAssign\n       ├─ Update DB: status='running', startedAt\n       ├─ Track in-memory: this.active[id] = {...}\n       └─ workerPool.assign(workerId, ExecAssign)\n\nWorker (Connected via WSS)\n  ├─ Receive ExecAssign\n  ├─ Executor.execute()\n  │   ├─ prepareSandbox()\n  │   ├─ injectCredentialsViaFile()\n  │   ├─ startFilterProxy() (if network policy)\n  │   ├─ spawn CLI process\n  │   ├─ Listen stdout/stderr\n  │   ├─ Wait for process exit\n  │   └─ Cleanup (sandbox, creds, proxy)\n  └─ Connection.sendComplete(status, exitCode, durationMs, ...)\n\nOrchestrator (Complete Event)\n  ├─ Dispatcher pool.on('complete')\n  ├─ Produce EXEC_LIFECYCLE to Kafka\n  ├─ Update DB:\n  │   ├─ status = 'completed'|'failed'|'cancelled'\n  │   ├─ completedAt, durationMs, costUsd\n  │   └─ Increment daily_metrics\n  ├─ Update in-memory: this.active[id].status\n  ├─ Schedule cleanup: delete from active (30s)\n  └─ processQueue() → dispatch next\n\nRe-queueing Paths:\n1. Worker Busy (NACK):\n   - Update DB: status='queued'\n   - Unshift to queue: front of line priority\n   - processQueue() → retry dispatch\n\n2. Worker Disconnect During Execution:\n   - If retries < 2:\n     - Update DB: status='queued', errorMessage=(retry X/2)\n     - Increment disconnectRetries counter\n     - Unshift to queue → processQueue()\n   - Else (retries exhausted):\n     - Update DB: status='failed', errorMessage=(exhausted)\n     - Produce EXEC_LIFECYCLE failure to Kafka\n\n3. Assignment Failure:\n   - Update DB: status='queued'\n   - Unshift to queue → processQueue()\n```\n\n### 6. RETRIES AND RECOVERY MECHANISMS\n\n#### Disconnect Retry Logic (dispatcher.ts, lines 214-281)\n- **Trigger**: Worker disconnects while executing\n- **Max Retries**: 2 (MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES)\n- **Tracking**: Via `disconnectRetries` counter in ActiveExecution\n- **DB Update**: Error message includes retry count: `Worker disconnected (retry 1/2)`\n- **Completion**: After 2 retries exhausted → permanent failure\n\n#### Busy Nack Retry (dispatcher.ts, lines 175-211)\n- **Trigger**: Worker sends 'busy' message (cannot accept assignment)\n- **Action**: Remove from active, re-queue to front, update DB to 'queued'\n- **Reason**: Worker hit internal constraints (concurrency, resource limits)\n\n#### Event Processing Retry (eventProcessor.ts, lines 299-317)\n- **Partial Delivery**: Some matches succeed, others fail/throttled\n- **Status**: 'partial-retry' or deferred for backoff retry\n- **Backoff**: Via `deferEventForRetry()` which uses exponential backoff\n- **Concurrency Limiting**: Per-persona max_concurrent enforcement\n\n#### Orphaned Event Recovery (eventProcessor.ts, lines 32-50)\n- **On Startup**: Reset all events in 'processing' state → 'pending'\n- **Periodic Reaping**: Every 60s, reset stale processing events (>120s old)\n- **Guard**: Prevents events stuck in processing from blocking forever\n\n### 7. LOGGING SUMMARY\n\n#### Current Logging Coverage\n\n| Phase | Level | Message | File:Line |\n|-------|-------|---------|-----------|\n| Submit | INFO | 'Execution submitted' | dispatcher.ts:343 |\n| Dispatch | INFO | 'Execution dispatched to worker' | dispatcher.ts:459 |\n| Complete (worker) | INFO | 'Execution finished' | executor.ts:243 |\n| Complete (pool) | INFO | 'Execution complete' | workerPool.ts:317 |\n| Event dispatch | INFO | 'Event dispatched to persona' | eventProcessor.ts:284 |\n| Stderr | WARN | 'Execution stderr' | dispatcher.ts:88 |\n| Worker busy | WARN | 'Worker rejected assignment' | dispatcher.ts:176 |\n| Disconnect retry | WARN | 'Worker disconnected, re-queueing' | dispatcher.ts:222 |\n| Retries exhausted | ERROR | 'Retries exhausted' | dispatcher.ts:254 |\n| DB operation fail | WARN | 'Failed to update execution status' | dispatcher.ts:184 |\n| Kafka produce fail | ERROR | 'Failed to produce to Kafka' | dispatcher.ts:102 |\n| Event tick | INFO | 'Event processor tick complete' | eventProcessor.ts:327 |\n\n#### Logging Context Pattern\n- Always includes `executionId` (or `eventId`) for correlation\n- Includes operation context: `op: 'updateExecution:queued'`\n- Phase information: `status: 'completed'`, `exitCode: 0`\n- Timing info: `durationMs`, `tickDurationMs`, `phaseTimings`\n- Worker context: `workerId` where relevant\n\n### 8. KEY EXECUTION-RELATED FILES\n\n#### Orchestrator Source\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts` (585 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/workerPool.ts` (412 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts` (337 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatchPipeline.ts` (267 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts` (183 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (341 lines)\n\n#### Worker Source\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/executor.ts` (273 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/connection.ts` (281 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/index.ts` (164 lines)\n\n#### Shared Source\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/types.ts` (347 lines)\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts` (230 lines)\n\nThis comprehensive analysis provides the foundation for understanding and enhancing the execution lifecycle tracking, logging, and state management across the entire personas-cloud system."}],"totalDurationMs":83417,"totalTokens":71013,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":296,"cache_read_input_tokens":65991,"output_tokens":4723,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":296},"inference_geo":"","iteration